                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep in mind that Agnis has to give out an integral number of roses to an integral number of girls, and he must give strictly more roses at each subsequent girl. To give roses to the most girls, Agnis would have to distribute the roses in fashion of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1, 2, 3 ,4... n"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". So, Agnis is giving out "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1+2+3+4+...+n"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" roses. So essentially, we're looking for the largest triangular number "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"T_n"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" such that "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"T_n = \frac{n(n+1)}{2} < 1000"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":", where "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is our answer, which happens to be "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\boxed{44}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



